<TITLE> One killed in AL-BNP clash over water body </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Meherpur, Feb 20 (bdnews24.com)  One person was killed and 34 others were injured local Awami League and BNP supporters fought over fishing rights at a public bheel, or water-body, at Gangni upazila in Meherpur district on Saturday. The dead man was identified as Sentu Miah, 35, a BNP activist. Gangni police chief Sagir Mian told bdnews24.com that clashes erupted when supporters of Shaharbati union BNP leader Zafar Ali and Awami League leader Nabiruddin, around 300 people in all, turned up "to fish" at the disputed Padma water-body in Milemari at around 8:30 am. There was an exsiting feud between Zafar and Nabir over control of the water-body, said the police chief. He said during Saturday's clash Awami League activists ransacked, looted and torched houses of BNP supporters Arshad Ali and Atiar Rahman. Fire fighters from Meherpur town were called in douse the blaze, he added. Police said three critically injured people  Azmine, 36, Zaharul, 45 and Amirul, 55  were admitted to Kushtia and Meherpur general hospitals. Sagir said police personnel were deployed in the area as tension was prevailing after the clash.
